Sent: Monday, March 08, 2004 8:44 AM
From: Col. John D Grabenstein <John.Grabenstein@otsg.amedd.army.mil>


I cited the Wiesen & Littell article for what it informs us regarding lack
of difference in rates of conception and rates of delivery (i.e. lack of
miscarriage) before or after anthrax vaccination. Among the 353 live
births, no unusual patterns were seen, but issues of statistical power do
apply, as the authors noted. This led to my comments about the pending
report of chart review and blinded analysis of birth defects being
performed jointly by the Naval Health Research Center and the Centers for
Disease Control & Prevention.

--
John Grabenstein
<John.Grabenstein@otsg.amedd.army.mil>

