[Mike has kindly offered to forward more information on the Australian
military problems with the UK vaccine as it comes available. Reading
between the lines of his comments it seems Australia may be a replay of the
vaccine side-effects sensitivity that we witnessed in the US a few years
ago. From what I saw when visiting a number of US Air National Guard units
at the time, that sensitivity reflected more the concerns of members of the
National Guard with prolonged periods abroad in a time of peace than actual
side-effect rates and severity -- and therefore of troop morale and
leadership. And as one can see from John's responses, the problem of
possible side-effects is under constant review in the US military. - Mod.MHJ]
